WEBVTT

00:41.097 --> 00:43.444
May I ask you something?

00:43.478 --> 00:46.102
I can't promise I'll answer.

00:47.655 --> 00:51.383
R... right, that's exactly
what I meant.

00:51.417 --> 00:55.145
Um, are you allowed to speak
along the way?

00:55.180 --> 00:57.975
I was thinking
there might be rules.

00:58.010 --> 00:59.770
Let me put it this way

00:59.805 --> 01:04.188
very few make it all the way
without uttering a word.

01:04.223 --> 01:07.606
People are overcome with
a strange and sudden need

01:07.640 --> 01:10.298
to confess on these trips.

01:10.333 --> 01:12.473
And not all of it
can be said to be

01:12.507 --> 01:15.096
of great rhetorical quality

01:15.131 --> 01:18.444
but do carry on merrily

01:18.479 --> 01:21.654
just don't believe you're
going to tell me something

01:21.689 --> 01:23.725
I haven't heard before.

01:33.459 --> 01:36.186
I will tentatively
divide my tale

01:36.221 --> 01:39.534
into five randomly
chosen incidents

01:39.569 --> 01:41.743
over a twelve-year period.

02:08.529 --> 02:12.049
So I'm standing here
holding this jack

02:12.084 --> 02:14.569
crap's not working.

02:14.604 --> 02:17.193
Do you, uh, do you have a jack
I could borrow?

02:17.227 --> 02:19.505
No, I'm sorry.

02:19.540 --> 02:21.024
- No?
- No

02:21.058 --> 02:22.715
- No?
- No

02:24.372 --> 02:28.135
That's odd,
I thought everyone had a jack.

02:28.169 --> 02:30.033
I don't.

02:30.067 --> 02:32.553
Perhaps you could
have a look at my car?

02:34.210 --> 02:37.868
Well, I don't have to
have a look at your car.

02:37.903 --> 02:40.768
The issue with your jack
is it's broken.

02:40.802 --> 02:42.045
There.

02:44.668 --> 02:49.604
So, uh, what's a person
like me supposed to do?

02:49.639 --> 02:53.470
Well, I suppose

02:53.505 --> 02:57.371
I could, uh, drive over
to Sonny's repair shop

02:57.405 --> 02:59.821
and call for roadside
assistance.

02:59.856 --> 03:03.170
It's about, uh,
five miles from here.

03:03.204 --> 03:04.654
What kind of repair shop is it?

03:04.688 --> 03:07.001
It's... it's..
Sonny's a blacksmith, very good one.

03:07.035 --> 03:09.279
Blacksmith.

03:09.314 --> 03:13.076
Well, maybe this Sonny can
repair the jack?

03:13.110 --> 03:15.147
You'd have to talk to Sonny
about that.

03:16.562 --> 03:19.738
Perhaps, I could entice you
to drive me there?

03:19.772 --> 03:21.912
- Please.
- Um..

03:44.038 --> 03:46.937
Oops, that was a mistake.

03:48.560 --> 03:49.595
Mistake?

03:49.630 --> 03:52.288
Me getting in this car
with you.

03:52.322 --> 03:53.472
What was it one's mother
used to say

03:53.496 --> 03:56.775
about not getting into cars
with strangers?

03:56.809 --> 03:58.984
Well..

03:59.018 --> 04:01.814
I wouldn't know what
your mother said.

04:01.849 --> 04:03.471
You might as well be
a serial killer.

04:05.059 --> 04:07.130
I'm sorry but you do kind of
look like one.

04:09.028 --> 04:10.754
You'd like me
to drive you back to your car?

04:12.308 --> 04:14.931
No, no.
I can take care of myself.

04:16.519 --> 04:18.762
I'm sorry,
were you offended

04:18.797 --> 04:20.625
that I called you
a serial killer?

04:21.869 --> 04:22.973
No.

04:24.251 --> 04:27.081
It's of absolutely
no importance to me.

04:30.464 --> 04:32.742
Maybe it's just the van.

04:32.776 --> 04:36.263
It's the kind one might expect
to be kidnapped in

04:36.297 --> 04:38.817
or used to transport corpses.

04:40.750 --> 04:42.648
But if you really were
a serial killer

04:42.683 --> 04:43.970
I guess the easiest thing
would be just

04:43.994 --> 04:48.930
to bury my body back up there
by those trees

04:48.965 --> 04:51.174
but you'd have to remember
to dig six feet down

04:51.208 --> 04:53.314
so the foxes couldn't
dig up my grave.

04:55.627 --> 04:58.388
What would I do?

04:58.423 --> 05:01.288
What would I do to keep you
from getting away with it?

05:02.979 --> 05:06.293
Of course, I'd just

05:06.327 --> 05:09.330
pick up that jack and hit you
over the head with it.

05:09.365 --> 05:11.194
A jack like that can do quite
a bit of damage

05:11.228 --> 05:12.437
don't you think?

05:14.818 --> 05:16.544
I'm not a medical examiner.

05:16.579 --> 05:18.960
It'd do quite a lot of damage.

05:39.602 --> 05:43.433
Don't forget this.
Good luck with Sonny.

05:43.468 --> 05:47.092
Um, would it be too much to ask
for you to drive me back?

05:47.126 --> 05:49.128
If this Sonny is as fast as
you say he is?

05:51.890 --> 05:54.168
I'm sure Sonny is perfectly
capable of giving you

05:54.202 --> 05:55.687
a lift back to your..

05:55.721 --> 05:57.792
As... as I told you before,
I don't like

05:57.827 --> 05:59.138
driving with strangers.

06:01.037 --> 06:03.453
Well, I'm just as much of
a stranger as Sonny is.

06:03.488 --> 06:04.868
Oh, getting along just fine.

06:04.903 --> 06:06.783
I'll just go speak to Sonny,
just take a moment.

06:19.573 --> 06:20.850
Sonny.

06:22.127 --> 06:23.887
Hi, Jack.

06:23.922 --> 06:25.026
How's it going?

06:25.061 --> 06:26.994
Well, I was working
on Miller's tractor

06:27.028 --> 06:30.273
but this lady is being
really persistent.

06:30.307 --> 06:31.343
You don't say.

06:42.181 --> 06:44.839
Big mistake.

06:44.874 --> 06:47.300
The reason serial killers can
roam around free in our country

06:47.324 --> 06:50.673
is that they have no connection
between themselves

06:50.707 --> 06:52.260
and their victims.

06:52.295 --> 06:54.815
So, you just made
a big mistake

06:54.849 --> 06:56.713
letting Sonny see
the two of us together.

07:08.691 --> 07:11.418
You know..

07:11.452 --> 07:14.386
...honestly,
I have more important things

07:14.421 --> 07:16.595
to be doing with my life

07:16.630 --> 07:19.115
than messing around
with this crap.

07:19.149 --> 07:21.635
You... you said
he was really good.

07:21.669 --> 07:23.844
Yeah, well,
I'm sure Sonny was just

07:23.878 --> 07:26.985
distracted by your
goddamned blabbering.

07:27.019 --> 07:29.228
Now I have to go,
I have an appointment.

07:29.263 --> 07:30.782
Appointment,
what appointment?

07:34.164 --> 07:36.235
That's none of your goddamn
business now, is it?

07:38.065 --> 07:40.239
You're not just gonna
leave me here.

07:40.274 --> 07:42.621
In fact, yes, that is kind of
what I was thinking.

07:45.106 --> 07:48.351
I'm sure there will be another
serial killer passing by

07:48.385 --> 07:50.629
who can give you a lift
back to Sonny's.

07:52.389 --> 07:56.808
That is, unless he decides
to kill you first.

07:59.051 --> 08:01.882
Even if I was to beg you
to drive me back?

08:01.916 --> 08:03.470
Just a last time?

08:04.712 --> 08:06.196
Pretty please.

08:20.728 --> 08:22.696
You know,
I take it all back

08:22.730 --> 08:26.044
what I said earlier about you
looking like a serial killer.

08:26.078 --> 08:28.771
No, no, no,
you don't have the disposition

08:28.805 --> 08:30.048
for that sort of thing.

08:31.532 --> 08:34.846
You're way too much
of a wimp to murder anyone.

08:51.172 --> 08:54.451
Oh, dear,
you are a dangerous man

08:54.486 --> 08:57.800
smacked her with a jack,
did you?

08:57.834 --> 09:00.147
Honestly, I've heard of
more murders

09:00.181 --> 09:02.908
than I can count.

09:02.943 --> 09:05.635
And by the way,
what does this ridiculous man

09:05.670 --> 09:07.706
have to do with anything?

09:07.741 --> 09:09.881
It's Glenn Gould

09:09.915 --> 09:12.539
one of the greatest piano
players of our time.

09:14.023 --> 09:15.921
He represents art.

09:20.616 --> 09:23.860
So a jack in the face of

09:23.895 --> 09:28.106
an admittedly unbearable lady
was great art.

09:28.140 --> 09:31.523
Is that what I'm to make of it?

09:31.558 --> 09:34.975
Dear Mr. Verge,
please give me a chance

09:35.009 --> 09:38.979
to cast some supplemental
light on the story of the jack.

09:39.013 --> 09:42.776
The old cathedrals often have
sublime artworks hidden away

09:42.810 --> 09:46.124
in the darkest corners
for only God to see

09:46.158 --> 09:48.713
or whatever
one feels like calling

09:48.747 --> 09:50.853
the great architect
behind it all.

09:52.302 --> 09:54.097
The same goes for murder.

09:58.343 --> 10:00.621
When I say cathedrals

10:00.656 --> 10:05.108
it is first and foremost the
gothic buildings we admire.

10:05.143 --> 10:08.525
Here elegant, pointed arches
have replaced the earlier

10:08.560 --> 10:11.494
more primitive rounded arches.

10:11.528 --> 10:15.636
The art of engineering is first
and foremost about statics

10:15.671 --> 10:18.432
that is so things remain
standing in spite of

10:18.466 --> 10:21.677
the various forces that impact
the buildings.

10:21.711 --> 10:26.474
In this way, the pointed arch
created a possibility to build

10:26.509 --> 10:29.823
much higher
and with much more light

10:29.857 --> 10:33.896
but most importantly
with less use of material.

10:33.930 --> 10:37.347
I often say that
the material does the work.

10:37.382 --> 10:40.868
In other words it has
a kind of will of its own

10:40.903 --> 10:44.044
and by following it,
the result will be

10:44.078 --> 10:45.459
the most exquisite.

10:46.840 --> 10:49.394
So the material was the jack

10:49.428 --> 10:53.156
and it jumped into the lady's
face on its own.

10:54.951 --> 10:56.643
Art is many things.

10:58.196 --> 11:00.819
Very convenient and unusual

11:00.854 --> 11:03.442
in the pile of bad excuses.

11:03.477 --> 11:06.204
But all of that
is of no interest whatsoever

11:06.238 --> 11:08.344
unless you're an engineer.

11:09.621 --> 11:11.105
I am an engineer.

11:19.113 --> 11:22.151
My mother was of the opinion
that becoming an engineer

11:22.185 --> 11:26.189
was the more financially
viable choice

11:26.224 --> 11:29.572
but my really big dream
was to become an architect.

11:35.164 --> 11:37.131
Right before the lady
and the jack

11:37.166 --> 11:38.926
I purchased a building lot

11:38.961 --> 11:42.067
and since
I was my own developer

11:42.102 --> 11:44.725
due to a substantial
inheritance

11:44.760 --> 11:47.624
no one could keep me
from drawing up

11:47.659 --> 11:50.662
my own plans
for my own house.

11:56.737 --> 12:00.223
Engineer or architect

12:00.258 --> 12:04.158
what I see is an OCD patient
in full bloom.

12:04.193 --> 12:07.058
Ordnungszwang Jack

12:07.092 --> 12:10.406
to use a good German word.

12:10.440 --> 12:13.029
Yes, perhaps, it is
in any case true

12:13.064 --> 12:16.377
that I suffered from
compulsions as a child.

12:16.412 --> 12:19.656
I was completely hysterical
about cleaning

12:19.691 --> 12:21.797
and could never leave
a room that wasn't

12:21.831 --> 12:23.764
perfectly neat and clean.

12:23.799 --> 12:26.698
A standard that was
difficult to maintain

12:26.733 --> 12:28.873
in the walk-in freezer.

12:28.907 --> 12:31.358
The walk-in freezer?

12:31.392 --> 12:34.119
The walk-in freezer
on Prospect Avenue.

12:34.154 --> 12:37.433
The sign has been broken
for forever

12:37.467 --> 12:40.263
so no one really knew what
the name of the street was.

13:09.361 --> 13:11.536
I bought the pizzas
from the former owner

13:11.570 --> 13:13.745
of the walk-in freezer.

13:13.780 --> 13:15.989
He claimed it was a great deal

13:16.023 --> 13:18.439
but of course I never managed
to sell them

13:18.474 --> 13:21.546
so it all became
too much for me.

13:21.580 --> 13:24.135
I only ate one of those
shitty pizzas.

13:26.689 --> 13:28.449
Pizza, pizza!

13:38.666 --> 13:41.704
And then there was a door
to another room

13:41.738 --> 13:44.293
which I never managed to open.

13:53.681 --> 13:57.754
A fucking neurotic riddled
with obsessive compulsions

13:57.789 --> 14:00.896
and a pathetic dream
of something greater.

14:18.810 --> 14:20.363
And what about the police?

14:20.398 --> 14:23.677
I imagine they started
coming around a lot.

14:27.750 --> 14:30.822
No, call it luck
if you will.

14:32.099 --> 14:34.343
I had attempted
to hide her car..

14:37.001 --> 14:39.589
...but to my great annoyance

14:39.624 --> 14:43.007
you could still catch a glimpse
of it from the main road.

14:45.941 --> 14:48.944
You know, without realizing
where I had parked the car

14:48.978 --> 14:50.669
was a stroke of genius.

14:50.704 --> 14:54.225
You see, the small brook
defines the state border

14:54.259 --> 14:55.951
and the local police,
per definition

14:55.985 --> 14:58.056
can't see across state lines.

14:58.091 --> 14:59.713
It's not their jurisdiction.

14:59.747 --> 15:02.785
So I had no inquiries
from the police.

15:02.819 --> 15:05.236
And by the way,
I don't even know if Sonny

15:05.270 --> 15:06.720
had told them about me.

15:06.754 --> 15:08.964
We met up quite
a few times since

15:08.998 --> 15:11.069
but never spoke of it.

16:43.092 --> 16:44.438
Hang on.

16:48.304 --> 16:49.961
Hi.

16:49.996 --> 16:50.997
Hi.

16:52.619 --> 16:54.517
Who are you?

16:54.552 --> 16:55.656
Police.

16:57.900 --> 16:58.901
Did something happen?

16:58.935 --> 17:00.213
Oh, no, no, no

17:00.247 --> 17:03.630
luckily nothing exactly
has happened as of yet.

17:03.664 --> 17:05.563
I understand that
you are fond of

17:05.597 --> 17:09.912
shopping at
Carlson's Supermarket.

17:09.945 --> 17:11.810
Why? Did something happen
at Carlson's?

17:11.845 --> 17:16.505
No, uh, however
we'd like to, uh, prevent

17:16.539 --> 17:20.542
things from happening
to businesses in the vicinity

17:20.578 --> 17:25.340
like Carlson's Supermarket.

17:26.894 --> 17:30.001
Yeah, may... may,
may I come in?

17:30.036 --> 17:32.279
I'd like to see
a police badge.

17:34.626 --> 17:35.903
So would I.

17:37.767 --> 17:40.184
Unfortunately, that today

17:40.218 --> 17:42.531
is going to be a bit of
a problem.

17:42.565 --> 17:44.429
Now, ahem..

17:44.464 --> 17:47.674
...I can tell by your expression

17:47.708 --> 17:49.020
that you think it's a bad thing

17:49.055 --> 17:52.196
that I don't have my police
badge on me.

17:52.230 --> 17:53.231
Right.

17:53.266 --> 17:54.415
Well, I'm here to tell you that

17:54.439 --> 17:55.992
it's a, it's a good thing..

17:58.236 --> 17:59.651
...for the police department

17:59.686 --> 18:01.653
and I'm not going to
lie to you, okay?

18:01.688 --> 18:03.183
It also happens to be
a good thing for me

18:03.207 --> 18:06.002
on a personal level. Yeah.

18:06.037 --> 18:10.317
You see my... my badge

18:10.352 --> 18:13.458
it's, uh, at the silversmith.

18:13.493 --> 18:15.426
Yeah, it's at the,
the silversmith.

18:15.460 --> 18:20.086
They're... they're shining it up
and, ah..

18:21.880 --> 18:25.401
...adding a few additional
citations to it.

18:25.436 --> 18:26.989
I've been promoted.

18:30.820 --> 18:33.029
- Okay.
- Right.

18:33.064 --> 18:35.031
So now you're..

18:35.066 --> 18:36.757
Now... now what are you?

18:36.792 --> 18:39.622
Like, what's your,
what's your rank now?

18:41.003 --> 18:43.626
We're not at liberty
to discuss that.

18:43.661 --> 18:46.284
Ah, that's considered
classified information.

18:46.319 --> 18:50.461
However, I think this is safe
to say that

18:50.495 --> 18:51.945
it's a considerable..

18:54.154 --> 18:55.397
...leap up the ladder.

18:57.330 --> 18:59.918
- Uh, ahem, now may I...
- No.

18:59.953 --> 19:02.438
Not without a badge.

19:03.646 --> 19:06.753
Bravo, bravo, bravo,
that's excellent.

19:06.787 --> 19:10.170
That's exactly just the type of
response we like to see.

19:10.205 --> 19:14.174
- You say no, that makes my day.
- Right.

19:14.209 --> 19:17.419
Of course, everybody's always
talking about security

19:17.453 --> 19:19.800
but what... what is actually
anybody doing about it?

19:19.835 --> 19:22.389
No, is quite
the correct answer.

19:22.424 --> 19:24.874
Yeah, it's quite
the correct answer indeed.

19:24.909 --> 19:28.430
Of course you'll never allow
somebody in your home

19:28.464 --> 19:31.053
just because they say,
"Oh, I'm a police officer."

19:31.087 --> 19:32.848
No. No, no, no.
You don't do that.

19:32.882 --> 19:34.574
No.

19:34.608 --> 19:36.817
You wait until they show you
the proper..

19:36.852 --> 19:40.096
- Badge.
- Yeah. The badge.

19:40.131 --> 19:42.651
- Yup.
- That's correct. Yeah.

19:42.685 --> 19:43.755
Um..

19:45.895 --> 19:49.278
May I, uh, ask you a..

19:50.348 --> 19:53.800
...ah, somewhat
personal question?

19:53.834 --> 19:57.252
Um, when exactly

19:57.286 --> 20:00.186
was it that you lost your,
your husband?

20:01.670 --> 20:05.708
It was just over
six months ago

20:05.743 --> 20:08.159
that my husband passed..

20:08.194 --> 20:09.885
Where are you going with this?

20:09.919 --> 20:12.750
Oh, I'm just thinking
about your..

20:12.784 --> 20:15.753
Your pension, yeah.

20:15.787 --> 20:18.687
I bet with a simple phone call
to one of my colleagues

20:18.721 --> 20:21.586
down in headquarters,
I could get you a, ah..

20:21.621 --> 20:24.037
...considerable increase
in your pension.

20:24.071 --> 20:25.970
I bet that I could,
I could double

20:26.004 --> 20:27.592
what you're currently receiving.

20:29.801 --> 20:31.389
Wait a minute.

20:33.322 --> 20:36.152
You could get me
double my pension

20:36.187 --> 20:38.154
from the police department
by calling people?

20:38.189 --> 20:40.674
Uh, forgive me, uh, uh..

20:40.709 --> 20:44.299
...I, I've tricked you, a bit.

20:44.333 --> 20:47.267
In fact, as it, as it stands

20:47.302 --> 20:50.960
I'm not,
I'm not a police officer.

20:50.995 --> 20:52.376
What?

20:52.410 --> 20:55.344
I'm an insurance agent, lady.

20:55.379 --> 20:58.313
The, the whole story
that I told you about the badge

20:58.347 --> 21:02.834
that's, t-that's something
that we've been asked to do

21:02.869 --> 21:06.459
by the authorities,
it's, it's for statistical

21:06.493 --> 21:08.323
purposes or something.

21:09.496 --> 21:12.050
- Hi, Glenn.
- Hi, Claire.

21:12.085 --> 21:14.639
- It's my friend Glenn.
- Glenn. Yeah, great guy.

21:14.674 --> 21:16.469
- You know Glenn?
- Yeah, sure.

21:16.503 --> 21:18.712
Uh, listen, are you interested

21:18.747 --> 21:21.336
in this, this increase,
uh, the money?

21:22.647 --> 21:24.615
Well, if you can double it.

21:24.649 --> 21:27.203
It won't take more than
a few minutes of your time.

21:27.238 --> 21:29.999
Alright, listen,
you can come in.

21:30.034 --> 21:32.347
This damn door sticks.

21:32.381 --> 21:34.152
I mean, what the heck's
the worst that could happen

21:34.176 --> 21:36.282
as long as you can
double my pension.

21:39.215 --> 21:41.666
Damn it.

21:41.701 --> 21:42.874
Something wrong?

21:45.498 --> 21:47.603
This is so damn humiliating.

21:50.157 --> 21:53.989
You know being forced
to, to stand out there

21:54.023 --> 21:57.717
exposed, time and time again

21:57.751 --> 22:01.997
have to be
put in these situations

22:02.031 --> 22:03.136
I don't know why.

22:03.170 --> 22:05.587
Listen, I'm sorry,
uh, I-I.. I was jus..

22:05.621 --> 22:07.623
You know
how humiliating it is?

22:07.658 --> 22:12.145
I am constantly being
put in these situations.

22:12.179 --> 22:13.629
It's just not fair.

22:13.664 --> 22:14.906
- No.
- Do you think it's fair?

22:14.941 --> 22:17.495
- No.
- No.

22:17.530 --> 22:18.748
Do you want me
to get you a cup of tea?

22:18.772 --> 22:21.706
Nah, nah, nah.
Don't worry about it.

22:28.230 --> 22:29.576
Ow! Fuck.

22:29.611 --> 22:33.891
Ow! Fuck. Ah, fuck. Fuck.

22:35.962 --> 22:37.757
The hell do you think
