44:17.814 --> 44:20.092
I loved when the men
from the village

44:20.127 --> 44:22.405
cut the meadows
with their scythes.

44:29.446 --> 44:32.380
Back then one spoke
of the breath of the meadow.

44:33.865 --> 44:35.729
Everyone working in rhythm

44:35.763 --> 44:38.870
exhaling when they mowed,
and inhaling when they pulled

44:38.904 --> 44:40.250
the scythes back.

45:03.549 --> 45:06.345
It was as if the meadow
lived at its fullest

45:06.380 --> 45:08.106
