53:50.283 --> 53:52.388
I sent the picture
to the local paper

53:52.423 --> 53:55.736
which usually distinguished
itself by running stories

53:55.771 --> 54:00.258
about missing, not to say,
uh, stolen garden gates

54:00.293 --> 54:03.744
and so, might do well
with a story with a, you know

54:03.779 --> 54:06.022
little more bite.

54:06.057 --> 54:08.922
For me though, what was really
sensational about the work

54:08.956 --> 54:11.511
with the photo,
it wasn't the image

54:11.545 --> 54:13.306
but the negative.

54:16.619 --> 54:18.828
When I was ten years old,
I discovered

54:18.863 --> 54:21.245
that through the negative,
you could see

54:21.279 --> 54:25.697
the real inner
demonic quality of the light.

54:25.732 --> 54:27.389
The dark light.

55:15.678 --> 55:19.510
But what about
repentance, Jack?

55:19.544 --> 55:23.376
The ones I deal with tend
to repent all over the place.

55:25.378 --> 55:27.311
I repent nothing

55:27.345 --> 55:29.934
no matter how long
we have to walk

55:29.968 --> 55:32.833
but I did think
of something the other day.

55:32.868 --> 55:36.147
Imagine a man
walking down a street

55:36.181 --> 55:38.667
underneath the street lamps.

55:38.701 --> 55:41.290
Right under a light
his shadow is the densest

55:41.325 --> 55:43.706
but also the tiniest.

55:43.741 --> 55:45.363
Then when he starts to move

55:45.398 --> 55:48.193
his shadow grows
in front of him.

55:48.228 --> 55:50.817
The shadow becomes
bigger and bigger

55:50.851 --> 55:54.027
while it thins out
and the shadow behind him

55:54.061 --> 55:56.581
from the next lamppost emerges

55:56.616 --> 55:59.481
and becomes
shorter and shorter

55:59.515 --> 56:01.931
until it reaches
its ultimate density

56:01.966 --> 56:05.728
as the man stands directly
underneath the light.

56:05.763 --> 56:07.420
Let's say that the man standing

56:07.454 --> 56:09.698
underneath the first lamppost
is me

56:09.732 --> 56:11.493
when I've just
committed a murder.

56:11.527 --> 56:14.599
I feel strong and content.

56:14.634 --> 56:18.914
I start to walk and the shadow
in front of me grows bigger

56:18.948 --> 56:21.882
like my pleasure,
but at the same time

56:21.917 --> 56:25.610
pain is on its way,
represented by the shadow

56:25.645 --> 56:28.302
behind me
from the next lamppost

56:28.337 --> 56:32.203
and at the midpoint
between the lampposts

56:32.237 --> 56:36.621
the pain is so great
it outweighs my pleasure.

56:36.656 --> 56:39.728
And with every step forward
pleasure dissolves

56:39.762 --> 56:42.524
and pain
intensifies behind me.

56:42.558 --> 56:46.631
Finally the pain
is so unbearably intense

56:46.666 --> 56:49.565
that I have to act,
so when I reach the point

56:49.600 --> 56:52.154
with the next lamp in zenith

56:52.188 --> 56:53.776
I will kill again.

56:55.502 --> 57:00.127
I know you want
to be someone special, Jack

57:00.162 --> 57:03.372
but let's face it,
this illustration can be used

57:03.407 --> 57:06.306
for any addict's tale of woe.

57:06.340 --> 57:09.067
The alcoholic empties
the bottle at the zenith

57:09.102 --> 57:10.690
et cetera, et cetera.

57:12.416 --> 57:14.348
But what about the family?

57:21.735 --> 57:24.600
I understand that your
occupation didn't leave

57:24.635 --> 57:27.500
