who's got some good pills.

01:31:14.219 --> 01:31:15.876
Are you leaving?

01:31:20.570 --> 01:31:23.400
I was just gonna go
get some pills.

01:31:31.581 --> 01:31:34.549
Do you have my... my keys?

01:31:34.584 --> 01:31:37.104
I'm not gonna take
some random pills.

01:31:41.453 --> 01:31:44.766
You know, I really think
I deserve better than this.

01:31:48.632 --> 01:31:50.565
I'm gonna hang on to the keys.

01:31:53.568 --> 01:31:56.019
It's a bad habit for you to

01:31:56.054 --> 01:31:58.573
go rushing downstairs
every time

01:31:58.608 --> 01:32:00.748
we start to have,
have a good time.

01:32:02.508 --> 01:32:03.751
Right?

01:32:06.823 --> 01:32:09.515
You're walking
without your crutch.

01:32:14.520 --> 01:32:17.592
And you weren't
using it downstairs either.

01:32:34.057 --> 01:32:37.267
You're Mr. Sophistication,
aren't you?

01:32:42.272 --> 01:32:44.067
If you feel like screaming..

01:32:45.655 --> 01:32:47.657
...I definitely think
that you should.

01:33:06.607 --> 01:33:08.436
You call that screaming?

01:33:09.679 --> 01:33:12.199
Help! Help!

01:33:14.304 --> 01:33:15.926
Help!

01:33:15.961 --> 01:33:18.032
Yes, help!

01:33:18.067 --> 01:33:20.621
There's a murderer
in the building!

01:33:20.655 --> 01:33:22.588
It's Mr. Sophistication!

01:33:22.623 --> 01:33:25.074
Help!

01:33:25.108 --> 01:33:27.076
Help!

01:33:29.112 --> 01:33:30.458
Shh!

01:33:32.150 --> 01:33:34.462
Shh! Hey.

01:33:34.497 --> 01:33:35.636
Hey. Hey.

01:33:37.120 --> 01:33:38.501
Shh!

01:33:49.891 --> 01:33:52.204
Do you hear?

01:33:52.239 --> 01:33:54.724
Do you hear anything?

01:33:54.758 --> 01:33:57.382
Do you hear anybody
running downstairs to help?

01:34:02.145 --> 01:34:04.734
Some neighbors you have.

01:34:04.768 --> 01:34:06.701
You want to try the window?

01:34:06.736 --> 01:34:08.979
I just want my keys.

01:34:11.120 --> 01:34:13.605
I just want my keys.

01:34:13.639 --> 01:34:15.227
I want my keys.

01:34:16.470 --> 01:34:18.886
Help!

01:34:18.920 --> 01:34:21.371
Help!

01:34:22.752 --> 01:34:25.444
Help me!

01:34:26.825 --> 01:34:29.207
Please help me!

01:34:44.291 --> 01:34:47.777
You know, maybe I'm mistaken,
but..

01:34:47.811 --> 01:34:49.399
...as far as I can tell..

01:34:51.367 --> 01:34:54.680
...not a single light
has gone on

01:34:54.715 --> 01:34:57.545
in any apartment or stairwell.

01:34:57.580 --> 01:34:58.891
You know why that is?

01:35:00.307 --> 01:35:03.689
'Cause in this hell of a town..

01:35:05.519 --> 01:35:07.245
...in this hell of a country..

01:35:09.316 --> 01:35:14.183
...in this hell of a world,
nobody wants to help!

01:35:19.498 --> 01:35:22.260
You can scream..

01:35:22.294 --> 01:35:25.573
...from now until Christmas Eve

01:35:25.608 --> 01:35:28.783
and the only answer
you'll get

01:35:28.818 --> 01:35:31.648
is the deafening silence
that you're hearing right now.

01:35:46.318 --> 01:35:48.044
Can't we talk?

01:35:49.908 --> 01:35:52.566
There's a time for talking

01:35:52.600 --> 01:35:55.465
and a time for being quiet.

01:35:55.500 --> 01:35:57.709
Open your mouth.

01:35:57.743 --> 01:35:59.400
Open your mouth!

01:36:33.503 --> 01:36:34.987
Okay, Simple.

01:36:35.022 --> 01:36:38.232
Oh, I'm sorry,
Ms. Jacqueline.

01:36:38.267 --> 01:36:41.649
Now, it's time..

01:36:43.133 --> 01:36:44.963
...for you to choose a knife.

01:36:46.171 --> 01:36:48.035
All you have to do is nod.

01:36:51.038 --> 01:36:52.419
No?

01:36:55.180 --> 01:36:56.423
What about this one?

01:36:57.769 --> 01:36:59.564
You don't like
that one either?

01:36:59.598 --> 01:37:00.772
Okay.

01:37:02.567 --> 01:37:04.189
How about this one?

01:37:07.019 --> 01:37:08.228
Hmm.

01:37:10.230 --> 01:37:11.610
Well..

01:37:13.957 --> 01:37:16.028
...that's an interesting
choice, Simple.

01:37:27.523 --> 01:37:29.110
You know..

01:37:30.905 --> 01:37:34.875
...there is something that has been
bothering Mr. Sophistication..

01:37:37.257 --> 01:37:39.604
...for quite a bit.

01:37:39.638 --> 01:37:42.365
And perhaps it's more
interesting to him..

01:37:44.160 --> 01:37:45.886
...than it would be to you.

01:37:48.233 --> 01:37:50.753
But to be honest

01:37:50.787 --> 01:37:53.963
he gets pretty fuckin' pissed
when he thinks about it.

01:37:55.102 --> 01:37:58.174
Why is it always
the man's fault?

01:38:00.970 --> 01:38:04.249
No matter where you go

01:38:04.284 --> 01:38:08.288
it's like you're some sort of
wandering guilty person.

01:38:11.463 --> 01:38:15.778
Without even having harmed
a single kitten.

01:38:19.368 --> 01:38:21.922
I actually get sad
when I think about it.

01:38:27.617 --> 01:38:30.965
If one is so unfortunate..

01:38:32.898 --> 01:38:36.419
...as to have been born male..

01:38:38.007 --> 01:38:40.320
...then you're also born guilty.

01:38:42.494 --> 01:38:44.876
Think of the injustice in that.

01:38:47.361 --> 01:38:49.777
Women are always
the victims, right?

01:38:53.160 --> 01:38:57.337
And men, they are always
the criminals.

01:39:21.875 --> 01:39:24.568
Told you before,
this is private property.

01:39:27.364 --> 01:39:28.779
I want you to leave.

01:39:33.128 --> 01:39:36.580
All the king's horses
and all the king's men

01:39:36.614 --> 01:39:39.617
couldn't put Simple
back together again.

01:39:41.964 --> 01:39:44.242
Why are they always so stupid?

01:39:45.278 --> 01:39:47.073
Who's stupid?

01:39:47.107 --> 01:39:52.078
All the women you kill strike
me as seriously unintelligent.

01:39:52.112 --> 01:39:53.493
Come on.

01:39:53.528 --> 01:39:55.322
I've also killed men.

01:39:55.357 --> 01:39:58.567
But you only talk
about the stupid women

01:39:58.602 --> 01:40:02.537
unless you think
all women are stupid.

01:40:02.571 --> 01:40:05.816
Well, the stories I've told
were selected at random, but...

01:40:05.850 --> 01:40:09.958
You feel superior to women
and want to brag?

01:40:09.992 --> 01:40:12.823
It turns you on,
doesn't it, Jack?

01:40:12.857 --> 01:40:15.342
No, no,
but women are easier.

01:40:15.377 --> 01:40:18.725
Not physically, they're
just easier to work with.

01:40:18.760 --> 01:40:20.071
More cooperative.

01:40:20.106 --> 01:40:21.901
To kill, you mean.

01:40:21.935 --> 01:40:23.661
If you like.

01:40:24.696 --> 01:40:27.319
Mr. Sophistication believes
in that theory.

01:40:27.353 --> 01:40:32.186
So, Mr. Sophistication
is, uh, the theoretician?

01:40:32.220 --> 01:40:33.567
I can tell
you're lapping it up

01:40:33.601 --> 01:40:36.224
when I tell you about
Mr. Sophistication.

01:40:36.259 --> 01:40:38.468
"So Jack hears voices

01:40:38.503 --> 01:40:41.229
"that order him
to do this or do that.

01:40:41.264 --> 01:40:43.369
Jack must be psychotic."

01:40:43.404 --> 01:40:46.407
I loathe diagnosis you can
just write down in letters.

01:40:48.202 --> 01:40:52.068
That's not fair,
the letters are clear.

01:40:52.102 --> 01:40:54.898
They look after us
and create boundaries

01:40:54.933 --> 01:40:58.592
between good and evil,
and they carry religion.

01:40:58.626 --> 01:41:01.387
Religion has ruined
human beings

01:41:01.422 --> 01:41:05.184
because your God teaches people
to deny the tiger in themselves

01:41:05.219 --> 01:41:08.325
and turns us all
into a throng of slaves

01:41:08.360 --> 01:41:10.466
too shameful to acknowledge it.

01:41:10.500 --> 01:41:12.675
Oh, Jack, you should have read

01:41:12.709 --> 01:41:15.263
the right letters in your life

01:41:15.298 --> 01:41:17.852
but you didn't want to.

01:41:17.887 --> 01:41:22.754
♪ Fame fame what you like
is in the limo ♪

01:41:22.788 --> 01:41:27.275
♪ Fame fame what you get
is no tomorrow ♪

01:41:27.310 --> 01:41:30.106
The collection of corpses were
mostly frozen

01:41:30.140 --> 01:41:31.556
shortly after death

01:41:31.590 --> 01:41:34.420
however, I think a handful
of them, by chance

01:41:34.455 --> 01:41:38.942
had reached, uh, at least, a
certain degree of putrefaction

01:41:38.977 --> 01:41:41.497
before I managed
to get them on ice.

01:41:41.531 --> 01:41:45.397
Can you say if putrefaction
is good or evil?

01:41:45.431 --> 01:41:48.573
Most people would say,
it's the natural breakdown

01:41:48.607 --> 01:41:51.196
which, in the end,
is a reaction of matter

01:41:51.230 --> 01:41:53.923
which is the basis for life
on earth.

01:41:53.957 --> 01:41:56.753
Thereby, it's neither
particularly good nor evil

01:41:56.788 --> 01:41:59.687
and that a human being must be
perceived as alive

01:41:59.722 --> 01:42:02.518
if you're to describe
that person's qualities

01:42:02.552 --> 01:42:05.693
and identify that person's
ultimate goal.

01:42:05.728 --> 01:42:08.351
But this is where
Mr. Sophistication

01:42:08.385 --> 01:42:11.319
has a very different opinion.

01:42:11.354 --> 01:42:14.081
He argues quite well
that the ultimate goal

01:42:14.115 --> 01:42:17.153
for the human being
is not prior to death

01:42:17.187 --> 01:42:18.706
but after.

01:42:18.741 --> 01:42:22.089
You reduce everything human
to matter

01:42:22.123 --> 01:42:25.748
and that way life disappears
and along with it art

01:42:25.782 --> 01:42:28.198
which you value so highly.

01:42:28.233 --> 01:42:32.168
Verge, you're a bitter
old bastard.

01:42:32.202 --> 01:42:36.413
You kill art by imposing
your moral ruler on life

01:42:36.448 --> 01:42:37.967
which I want to free

01:42:38.001 --> 01:42:40.625
because art is so immeasurably
vaster

01:42:40.659 --> 01:42:42.316
than we will ever understand.

01:42:42.350 --> 01:42:44.111
May I illustrate now?

01:42:44.145 --> 01:42:47.666
There is no avoiding it,
is there?

01:42:52.119 --> 01:42:55.467
I don't have a handle on
how many processes take part

01:42:55.501 --> 01:42:58.332
in the decay of a dead human

01:42:58.366 --> 01:43:00.714
but I know a bit
about dessert wines.

01:43:02.370 --> 01:43:05.166
In order to achieve
the most sublime sweetness

01:43:05.201 --> 01:43:07.686
and the greatest wines,
nature has provided us

01:43:07.721 --> 01:43:09.067
with various methods.

01:43:10.551 --> 01:43:14.106
The three most common forms
of decomposition are

01:43:14.141 --> 01:43:16.039
frost..

01:43:16.074 --> 01:43:18.007
...dehydration..

01:43:18.041 --> 01:43:19.698
...and a fungus
with the enticingly

01:43:19.733 --> 01:43:22.494
mysterious name,
the noble rot.

01:43:29.639 --> 01:43:32.297
The first method is the one
that in Germany

01:43:32.331 --> 01:43:34.886
is used to produce "Eiswein."

01:43:34.920 --> 01:43:36.957
The method
quite simply entails

01:43:36.991 --> 01:43:39.304
leaving the grapes on the vine
for so long

01:43:39.338 --> 01:43:43.066
that they are exposed to frost
for a certain number of nights

01:43:43.101 --> 01:43:44.550
before they are pressed.

01:43:44.585 --> 01:43:47.243
This method increases
the sugar content

01:43:47.277 --> 01:43:49.625
in the wine dramatically.

01:43:49.659 --> 01:43:53.490
It is very risky,
as the grapes must have certain qualities

01:43:53.525 --> 01:43:56.562
in order to be able to
withstand the process.

01:43:56.597 --> 01:43:58.668
On top of that,
there can be uncertainty

01:43:58.703 --> 01:44:01.015
about whether or not the first
night's frost

01:44:01.050 --> 01:44:05.606
lives up precisely to the
expectations, et cetera.

01:44:05.641 --> 01:44:08.920
The second method
is called "Trockenbeeren"

01:44:08.954 --> 01:44:11.508
in which the grapes are
allowed to hang on the vine

01:44:11.543 --> 01:44:15.961
until they dry up and very
nearly become raisins.

01:44:15.996 --> 01:44:18.308
The last method,
which, for example

01:44:18.343 --> 01:44:21.415
is essential for the
production of Sauternes

01:44:21.449 --> 01:44:23.659
is a kind of mold
that causes grapes

01:44:23.693 --> 01:44:25.764
to be very full-bodied

01:44:25.799 --> 01:44:30.044
and have an explosively high
sugar content.

01:44:30.079 --> 01:44:32.460
You could say about
all three processes

01:44:32.495 --> 01:44:34.600
that it's the breakdown
that lifts the living grape

01:44:34.635 --> 01:44:36.361
up to be a part of an artwork.

01:44:37.914 --> 01:44:40.952
You can view the processes
that start in a human being

01:44:40.986 --> 01:44:43.195
after death in the same manner.

01:44:43.230 --> 01:44:48.269
Says you! And I still say that
without love there is no art.

01:44:48.304 --> 01:44:51.031
It's not up for debate.

01:44:51.065 --> 01:44:53.723
The thing you are talking
about with the grapes

01:44:53.758 --> 01:44:57.278
is just nature's
method of decomposing.

01:44:57.313 --> 01:45:01.731
If decomposition
is a way to salvation

01:45:01.766 --> 01:45:03.975
then what about your house?

01:45:05.148 --> 01:45:07.530
By God, you cannot convince me

01:45:07.564 --> 01:45:10.636
that the idea of your first
house being torn down

01:45:10.671 --> 01:45:13.018
was, in any way, satisfying.

01:45:13.053 --> 01:45:16.815
Do you claim that
it was built to be torn down?

01:45:18.127 --> 01:45:20.716
No, of course it wasn't ideal

01:45:20.750 --> 01:45:22.476
and I'm sorry to say
that it happened

01:45:22.510 --> 01:45:24.581
no less than three more times

01:45:24.616 --> 01:45:28.137
that I started construction
and then became doubtful.

01:45:28.171 --> 01:45:30.346
It was difficult to create
the house

01:45:30.380 --> 01:45:31.865
that I had dreamed of.

01:45:31.899 --> 01:45:34.868
The material didn't do
what I wanted it to do.

01:45:34.902 --> 01:45:37.456
The houses I had drawn
had already

01:45:37.491 --> 01:45:39.907
at the very first detail,
something banal

01:45:39.942 --> 01:45:41.944
not to say ordinary,
about them

01:45:41.978 --> 01:45:46.465
Isn't that what in art
you would call epigonism?

01:45:46.500 --> 01:45:49.606
Your great talent
only reached so far

01:45:49.641 --> 01:45:52.161
you, artist of all times.

01:45:53.541 --> 01:45:56.372
When you were writing,
didn't you yourself plan

01:45:56.406 --> 01:45:59.064
the destruction of your most
popular literary work?

01:46:00.307 --> 01:46:02.792
"The Aeneid"
was a commissioned work

01:46:02.827 --> 01:46:07.176
where the ruling power and
its ideas were glorified by me

01:46:07.210 --> 01:46:11.111
to the point
where it was no longer art.

01:46:11.145 --> 01:46:14.252
But if glorification
could demean a work..

01:46:15.943 --> 01:46:17.980
...why should destruction
and demolition

01:46:18.014 --> 01:46:21.397
not be able to do the opposite
and create art?

01:46:23.364 --> 01:46:26.574
Albert Speer invented
"The Theory of Ruin Value"

01:46:26.609 --> 01:46:29.336
by examining the Greek
and Roman ruins

01:46:29.370 --> 01:46:32.822
and constructed his buildings
using both weaker

01:46:32.857 --> 01:46:34.479
and stronger materials

01:46:34.513 --> 01:46:37.309
so that they, in a thousand
years, would appear

01:46:37.344 --> 01:46:39.277
as aesthetically perfect ruins.

01:46:40.761 --> 01:46:43.384
Which fortunately
were smashed to atoms

01:46:43.419 --> 01:46:47.733
in mere few years
after their construction.

01:46:47.768 --> 01:46:51.185
Hubris is punished by nemesis

01:46:51.220 --> 01:46:54.257
if I may use an old-fashioned
expression.

01:46:54.292 --> 01:46:56.225
But an artist must be cynical

01:46:56.259 --> 01:47:00.470
and not worry about the welfare
of humans or Gods in his art.

01:47:00.505 --> 01:47:02.714
This talk about
the value of ruins

01:47:02.748 --> 01:47:06.614
makes it too obvious, not to
mention, another subject.

01:47:06.649 --> 01:47:08.133
The value of icons.

01:47:26.255 --> 01:47:27.843
The Stuka

01:47:27.877 --> 01:47:30.776
without a doubt the world's
most beautiful airplane

01:47:30.811 --> 01:47:35.057
and to top it off featuring an
eerily sophisticated detail.

01:47:35.091 --> 01:47:37.783
I'm sure you know
what I'm talking about.

01:47:37.818 --> 01:47:41.546
No, by God
that has never interested me

01:47:41.580 --> 01:47:43.824
but do tell me about it.

01:47:43.859 --> 01:47:45.688
The Stuka was a dive-bomber.

01:47:45.722 --> 01:47:47.932
They say that the pilots
actually passed out

01:47:47.966 --> 01:47:50.313
for a brief moment
during the actual dive.

01:47:50.348 --> 01:47:53.282
But the detail per favore.

01:47:53.316 --> 01:47:54.939
Fantastic.

01:47:54.973 --> 01:47:56.354
Incomparable.

01:47:56.388 --> 01:47:59.081
Notice the sound
when the plane dives.

01:47:59.115 --> 01:48:01.531
The screeching sound.

01:48:01.566 --> 01:48:05.397
A result of poor design
if you ask me.

01:48:05.432 --> 01:48:08.331
Poor design, please.

01:48:08.366 --> 01:48:12.370
On the contrary,
the screeching was intrinsic

01:48:12.404 --> 01:48:15.821
sirens were attached to
the undercarriage of the plane

01:48:15.856 --> 01:48:20.792
purposely designed as a
psychological act of war.

01:48:20.826 --> 01:48:24.969
No one who heard it in action
will ever forget that sound.

01:48:25.003 --> 01:48:27.903
It made the blood run cold
in everyone's veins.

01:48:28.869 --> 01:48:30.906
Known as Jericho's Trumpet.

01:48:32.977 --> 01:48:35.772
Sadistic, but in your eyes

01:48:35.807 --> 01:48:38.189
probably a masterpiece.

01:48:38.223 --> 01:48:42.020
No, more than a masterpiece.

01:48:42.676 --> 01:48:44.678
An icon.

01:48:44.712 --> 01:48:47.543
The person or persons,
who conceived the Stuka

01:48:47.577 --> 01:48:51.029
and its functions,
were icon-creators.

01:48:51.064 --> 01:48:52.893
What I'm getting at is this

01:48:52.928 --> 01:48:54.653
as disinclined
as the world is

01:48:54.688 --> 01:48:57.656
to acknowledge
the beauty of decay

01:48:57.691 --> 01:49:01.039
it's just as disinclined
to give credit to those

01:49:01.074 --> 01:49:03.593
no credit to us

01:49:03.628 --> 01:49:06.217
who create the real icons
of this planet.

01:49:07.701 --> 01:49:09.289
We are deemed
the ultimate evil.

01:49:13.638 --> 01:49:17.849
All the icons that have had
and always will have

01:49:17.883 --> 01:49:19.540
an impact on the world

01:49:19.575 --> 01:49:22.198
are for me extravagant art.

01:49:34.486 --> 01:49:36.143
The noble rot.

01:49:36.178 --> 01:49:40.458
Stop it... you Antichrist!

01:49:40.492 --> 01:49:42.978
I don't recall ever having
escorted

01:49:43.012 --> 01:49:47.016
a so thoroughly depraved
person as you, Jack.

01:49:50.485 --> 01:49:53.695
Since you have now apparently
set your heart

01:49:53.729 --> 01:49:56.145
in mass extermination

01:49:56.180 --> 01:49:58.493
let me make a brief comment

01:49:58.527 --> 01:50:01.047
about the Buchenwald camp

01:50:01.081 --> 01:50:06.293
that emphasizes my attitude
towards art and love.

01:50:06.328 --> 01:50:10.574
In the middle of this
concentration camp stood a tree

01:50:10.608 --> 01:50:13.335
and not just any old tree,
but an oak

01:50:13.369 --> 01:50:16.994
and not just any oak,
but the one Goethe

01:50:17.028 --> 01:50:18.685
when he was young,
